codecrypt
------------------------------------------
This is a GnuPG-like unix program for encryption and signing that uses only
quantum-computer-resistant algorithms.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libbsd0-0.11.7-3
  libfftw3_3-3.3.10-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libgmp10-6.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libbsd-devel-0.11.7-3
  libfftw3-devel-3.3.10-1
  libgmp-devel-6.3.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://gitea.blesmrt.net/exa/codecrypt

Canonical download:
  https://gitea.blesmrt.net/exa/codecrypt.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack codecrypt-1.8+git20220925-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./codecrypt-1.8+git20220925-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/codecrypt-1.8+git20220925-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/codecrypt-1.8+git20220925-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(codecrypt)
  /usr/bin/ccr.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/codecrypt.README
  /usr/share/doc/codecrypt/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/codecrypt/COPYING.LESSER
  /usr/share/doc/codecrypt/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/codecrypt/README
  /usr/share/doc/codecrypt/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/ccr.1.gz

